We know that when you smoke a cigarette you are absorbing about 1 mg of nicotine. If you smoke a half pack per day, your are taking in about 10 mg of nicotine per day. Pack per day smokers are taking in about 20 mg of nicotine per day. Those with a two-pack habit are taking in 40 mg per day and so on and so forth.
